The Edit command in UG is not changed after some new Edit commands
are introduced.

Users will not know the new Edit commands from current UG.

Updating Edit command in UG allows users to learn how to use new
Edit commands.

Let's update the Edit Commands in UG to support smooth usage of our
application for our users.

DG Logic component is not modified yet to represent our new
implementation.

A up-to-date DG helps developers develop future features correctly
based on current implementation.

Adding diagrams helps explaining the implementation.

Let's update DG Logic component as well as adding class diagrams for
better and accurate explanation of the Logic component.

Diagrams aid presentation of the implementation of the Logic component
better than only words.

commitResults.messageTitle: Tree Command: Display LinkTree in A New Window
commitResults.messageBody:
Our hierarchy of contact information are not visualizable.

Visualization of hierachy of contact information aids the user to make
decisions.

Visualizing the tree structure provides a general hierarchical view of
all the contact information, which helps users to decide who to
contact.

Let's have a "tree" command that allows users to see the tree
structure in a new window.

Displaying in a new window allows bigger display of the tree structure
so that users can navigate easily.
Tree Command: Display LinkTree in A New Window

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix Bug: Crash after Edit Command
commitResults.messageBody:
There will be a NullPointerException after using edit command to
change a person's information. Becuase edit command will create a
new person object which will have a new Identity code, old Identity
code stored in the team book cannot refer to the edited person
which has a new Identity code.

The tree command cannot work with the exception present.

Let's fix this bug so that "LinkTree" can be shown properly after
edit command. Let's have new person constructor that instantiate
a person object with a given identity code.

Therefore, edit command can create a new person object with
original Identity code.
Fix Bug: Crash after Edit Command

The tree command description in the UG is not up to date.

pictures for demonstration.

Pictures can help users understand the result of the command
better.

commitResults.messageBody:
The current implementation lacks functionality to specifically find a
team and its leader by their respective attributes.

To enhance the search capabilities of the application, it's necessary
to provide commands that allow users to efficiently retrieve teams and
their leaders based on given criteria.

Let's,
* add the `FindTeamCommand` and `FindTeamLeaderCommand` classes
* implement parsers for both commands to handle user input
* extend the `Messages` class to support new error and success messages
  for these commands

The decision to have separate classes for each command ensures modularity
and separation of concerns. It also paves the way for potential future
enhancements specific to each command.
Add FindTeam and FindTeamLeader command classes

The project lacked a visual representation of the storage component's architecture.

Having a UML diagram aids developers in understanding the structural relationships between storage classes and interfaces.

Let's introduce a PlantUML file named `storage.puml` that provides a detailed UML diagram for the storage component of the project.

Using PlantUML allows for easy updates to the diagram in future iterations, ensuring maintainability and clarity for the development team.

- Refactored and improved test cases for `TeamBook.java` within the model package. - Enhanced testing for `Team.java` ensuring better coverage and edge case handling. - Added predicate tests for keyword searches in `TeamContainsKeywordsPredicate.java`. - Revamped serialization tests for `JsonSerializableTeamBook.java` to ensure data integrity during serialization. - Extended testing coverage for command logic with `AddCommandTest.java`. - Improved test data samples in:   - `duplicateTeamTeamBook.json`   - `invalidTeamBook.json`   - `typicalTeamsTeamBook.json`   - `invalidAndValidTeamTeamBook.json`   - `invalidTeamTeamBook.json`   - `notJsonFormatTeamBook.json`   - `validTeamBook.json` - Amplified storage-related test scenarios with:   - `JsonAdaptedTeamTest.java`   - `JsonSerializableTeamBookTest.java`   - `JsonTeamBookStorageTest.java`
commitResults.messageBody: These changes ensure robustness and accuracy in the team management module, paving the way for future enhancements and feature integrations.
Update: Enhanced Test Coverage for Team Management Module

Update: Revamped GUI Integration for "Find" Command Functionality

- Enhanced user interface interactions for the general `FindCommand.java`.
- Optimized visualization and feedback mechanisms for the `FindTeamCommand.java`, ensuring users receive clear and concise results when searching for teams.
- Overhauled the graphical representation and output for `FindTeamLeaderCommand.java`, enhancing the user experience when locating team leaders within the application.

These GUI updates provide a more intuitive and streamlined user experience, allowing for easier navigation and improved efficiency when utilizing the "find" commands.
Update: Revamped GUI Integration for "Find" Command Functionality

This commit addresses several bugs and issues in the FindTeamCommand and FindTeamLeaderCommand classes.

These fixes improve the reliability and accuracy of both FindTeamCommand and FindTeamLeaderCommand, ensuring that they work as intended and provide better user feedback when encountering issues. Unit tests have also been updated to cover these scenarios to prevent regressions in the future.
